com.pump.io.location

Class CachedLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.io.location.IOLocation
      • com.pump.io.location.CachedLocation
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultSearchResults, FileLocation, Pics4LearningLocation, SpotlightIOLocation, URLLocation

    public abstract class CachedLocation
extends IOLocation
    This is an IOLocation that caches most simple properties (include children) for immediate return.

    It's tempting to think that these calls should generally be fast, but we've seen java.io.File.exists() stall for several seconds at a time when the file system is experiencing network connectivity problems.

    By caching all of these values: it becomes imperative that you invoke flush() at the appropriate times to clear cached data. For example: after writing, deleting or renaming a file the data should be flushed. You might also consider flushing cached data when a file navigation dialog is reactivated (because the user might have just switched from the OS back to the app after manipulating files). But the other 90% of the time: the cached value should be reasonably trustworthy.

      • flush

        public void flush()
        Description copied from class: IOLocation
        This flushes any cached information about this location. Some locations may cache several properties: the children, isHidden, exists, etc. This method should be called when we know that something has changed and all cached values should be purged.
        Overrides:
        flush in class IOLocation

      • listChildren

        public final IOLocation[] listChildren(Receiver<IOLocation> receiver,
                                       BasicCancellable cancellable)
        This method starts a separate thread that gathers and caches the children of this location. Subsequent calls to listChildren() will return immediately, unless flush() has cleared the cached data of this IOLocation.

        TODO: take into account the last modified time.

        Specified by:
        listChildren in class IOLocation
        Parameters:
        receiver - an optional Receiver to be notified as each child is processed.
        cancellable - an optional Cancellable. If non-null: classes that extend this class should constantly poll it to see if isCancelled() is true.
        Returns:
        all the children (if any) of this object. This should not return null, but may return an empty array for non-directories.
        See Also:
